    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="https://norfolk.craigslist.org/apa/d/norfolk-loft-with-bay-views-furnished/7514922154.html"></div>
        </div>
Month-to-Month or 6 Month Leases<br>
<br>
Available from September 15 through March 15 these 1 and 2 bedroom high-end, custom beach vacation rentals are available for rent during the off-season. The properties are on the beach in Willoughby and they are not part of an apartment complex. Rent includes all utilities (water sewer, electric/hear/air, cable television and wifi), linens, and housewares. They are professionally decorated and fully furnished (all rental have sleeper sofas in addition to king size beds in bedrooms). The fully equipped kitchen feature full-size oven, full-size refrigerator with ice-maker, dishwasher, microwave oven, coffee maker, electric tea kettle, toaster and every item need for a comfortable stay. The rentals also include washer/dyer in every rental, ceiling fans, individually controlled central heating/cooling systems, 2 to 3 60-inch TV's, and there is plenty of parking.<br>
<br>
The Loft rental has a 400 square foot deck that has views of the Chesapeake Bay. The cottage has a wrap around porch and decking. These are both 2 bedroom rentals located at our Beach Cottage property at 900 W Ocean View Avenue and lease for $3,000 to $3,500 per month. The loft has 1,000 square feet of living space and the ground floor cottage has 1,200 square feet of living space.<br>
<br>
Our Poseidon property has three 1-bedroom rentals. There is a Carriage House (600 square feet), a Court Yard Cottage (800 square feet) and a Beachfront rental (1,200 square feet with sauna and fireplace) there. Depending on the unit rates are $2,500 to $3,500 per month<br>
<br>
Both properties are historical beach cottage properties that are over 100-years old. We have restored them and have maintained the original ambience and authenticity of these places. They are charming and original wood floors where we could salvage them (but all have wood floors whether they are 100 years old or new), wainscotting, and plaster walls<br>
<br>
The properties are side-by-side and share common spaces that includes extensive outdoor seating and landscape areas, Bocce Ball Court, Horse Shoe Pit, Corn Hole, large seating deck around a fountain, beachfront recreational kitchen with running water, hot tub, and beachfront pergola<br>
<br>
Our neighborhood is centrally located and served with 2 interstate interchanges for I-64. We are 10-minutes from the Little Creek, Norfolk Naval Base, Norfolk International Airport, Old Dominion University, Downtown Hampton, and Hampton University. We are less than 15 minutes away from Downtown Norfolk, Sentara Norfolk General Hospital, Norfolk State University and Eastern Virginia Medical School<br>
<br>
To see this property please call or text John  <a href="#" class="show-contact" title="click to show contact info" data-href="/reply/nfk/apa/7514922154/__SERVICE_ID__" rel="nofollow">show contact info</a>
 (owner/agent)
